# Styling & theming (Tailwind v4 + shadcn tokens)

## How theming works here
- Tailwind v4, **CSS-first**. `src/app/globals.css` imports `tailwindcss`, `tw-animate-css`, and
  `shadcn/tailwind.css`, then defines the theme as **CSS variables in `oklch`** under `:root` and
  `.dark`. There is **no `tailwind.config.js`** — don't create one. Radius scales from `--radius`;
  headings use `font-heading`.

## Use semantic tokens, never hardcoded colors
`bg-background`/`text-foreground`, `bg-card`/`text-card-foreground`, `bg-primary`/`text-primary-foreground`,
`text-primary`, `bg-secondary`, `bg-muted`/`text-muted-foreground`, `bg-accent`/`text-accent-foreground`,
`text-destructive`/`bg-destructive`, `border` (border-border), `ring-ring`. **Never** `sky-600`, `slate-900`, etc.

## Re-theming for a new client (the money move)
- To rebrand, edit `--primary`, `--ring`, and optionally `--accent` in **both** `:root` and `.dark`
  in `globals.css`. Every token-styled element updates at once. Never hardcode a brand color in a component.

## Dark mode
- `next-themes` with `attribute="class"` (`.dark`). `ThemeProvider` wraps the app in `layout.tsx`,
  which sets `suppressHydrationWarning` on `<html>` — keep both. Token styling is dark-ready by default;
  add `dark:` utilities only for genuine special cases.

## Layout patterns (reuse)
- Page container: `mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4 sm:px-6`; sections `py-16`. Mobile-first, then `sm:`/`md:`/`lg:`.
- Prefer composing shadcn `Card` over hand-built bordered boxes; size icons with `size-*`.
